# There are a few things you should know if making a map for this gamemode.
#
# First, it is necessary to have sands defined for the resources in the following slots:
# 31 - Ore
# 32 - Redon
# 33 - Greenar
# 34 - Spectrite
# This is so fissures can pick the correct colour for their designated resource. You can use the export JSON
# option in the sand interactions panel to export the sand definitions of an existing map.
#
# Second, making fissures requires you to edit variables using the in-game variable editor. You can do this
# by selecting the unit in the editor, clicking on the button under "scripts" and modifying the values
# highlighted in green. The resource is defined using the values 31-34 as stated previously.
#
# Third, be careful with particulate as the ship placement logic is blind to it. Part emitters should only
# exist in places which have creeper.
#
# Any new ships must have definitions in unitcontrol.irpl for their rectangular size, and if they are to
# be controlled by the frontline system they must also have a "maxDistance" set. maxDistance is the
# maximum number of frontline cells a ship will try to place itself away from the creeper. Frontline
# cells can be seen by checking "Show Frontlines" in the RTS editor UI.
